  "content": "### Structured Log Events\n### ProcessingReport (returned to caller)\n\n## Dependency Chain\n\n```\nM3.3 (Chunking) has NO hard dependency on M3/M3.1/M3.2\n  - Shares TokenEstimator with M3.2 (D64)\n  - M3.2's Retriever consumes chunks M3.3 produces\n  - Can be built in parallel with M3.1/M3.2\n```\n\n\n## Test Strategy\n\n| Component | Approach |\n|-----------|----------|\n| `ChunkingPipeline` | Unit test: mock strategy, verify merge/split/overlap orchestration |\n| `FormatRegistry` | Unit test: register/override/resolve priority chain |\n| `AstChunker` | Unit test: known Rust/Python/JS files → expected chunks (migrate existing tree-sitter tests) |\n| `MarkdownChunker` | Unit test: heading hierarchy → sections, oversized section splitting |\n| `ConfigChunker` | Unit test: TOML/YAML/JSON → key-based chunks |\n| `PdfChunker` | Unit test: extracted text → paragraph chunks |\n| `FallbackChunker` | Unit test: recursive separator cascade |\n| `TokenEstimator` | Unit test: chars/4 heuristic, budget enforcement |\n| Merge pass | Unit test: small chunks merge, respects merge_group, stops at budget |\n| Split pass | Unit test: oversized chunks recurse, all outputs fit budget |\n| E2E integration | Ingest real repo through full pipeline, verify chunk quality metrics |\n",
